race.comment: COME ON GLAMOUR (5) was dominant first-up at Grafton, leading throughout and never giving her rivals a look-in. Sure to be improved with that run under the belt and can go on with the job. COSMIC COCO (1) resumes after chasing strongly into the placings on stable debut against tougher opposition before spelling. Readied with a quiet trial and aided by the claim, he can make a bright return. NESCAFFIER (2) also resumes and looks to have come back in good order with two solid trials. The Mallyon booking is a strong push and from a low draw he can give this a big shake. PIEDI VELOCI (3) ended last campaign with a gritty maiden win at this track. No reason he can't pick up where he left off.
